  "prompt": "Who are the greatest pianists of our age?",
  "response": "The title of \"greatest pianists of our age\" is subjective and can vary based on personal taste and musical style. However, several pianists have garnered widespread acclaim and recognition for their exceptional talent and contributions to music in recent years. Some of these include:\n\n1. **Martha Argerich** - Renowned for her virtuosity and passionate playing, particularly in the Romantic repertoire.\n\n2. **Lang Lang** - A global superstar known for his charismatic performances and versatility, appealing to both classical and contemporary audiences.\n\n3. **Yuja Wang** - Celebrated for her technical prowess and expressive interpretations, she brings a modern flair to classical music.\n\n4. **Daniil Trifonov** - A young virtuoso recognized for his deep musicality and technical skill, gaining attention in both solo and chamber music.\n\n5. **Igor Levit** - Known for his insightful interpretations and commitment to contemporary music alongside the classical canon.\n\n6. **Murray Perahia** - A distinguished pianist celebrated for his interpretations of Bach, Beethoven, and Chopin, as well as his work as a conductor.\n\n7. **Richard Goode** - Renowned for his interpretations of Beethoven and the Classical repertoire, Goode is highly respected in the piano community.\n\n8. **Pierre-Laurent Aimard** - Acclaimed for his expertise in both the classical repertoire and contemporary works.\n\n9. **Emanuel Ax** - A leading pianist known for his collaborations and solo performances, especially in chamber music settings.\n\n10. **Andr\u00e1s Schiff** - Revered for his interpretations of Bach and Beethoven, Schiff is also noted for his insightful approach to musical pedagogy.\n\nThese musicians represent a variety of styles and traditions, and their influence on the piano world is significant. The list is certainly not exhaustive, and there are many other talented pianists who have made substantial contributions to music today.",
